\begin_inset Formula $\theta\in\Theta_{0}^{c}$
\end_inset

.
 Except in trivial situations, this ideal cannot be attained.
 Qualitatively, a good test has a power function near 1 for most 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta\in\Theta_{0}^{c}$
\end_inset

 and near 0 for most 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta\in\Theta_{0}$
\end_inset

.
